{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":793,"text":"What do you do when you have a headache?"},{"time":3832,"text":"You swallow an aspirin."},{"time":6247,"text":"But for this pill to get\nto your head, where the pain is,"},{"time":10594,"text":"it goes through your stomach, intestines\nand various other organs first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16947,"text":"Swallowing pills is the most effective\nand painless way of delivering"},{"time":22093,"text":"any medication in the body."},{"time":25452,"text":"The downside, though, is that swallowing\nany medication leads to its dilution."},{"time":31134,"text":"And this is a big problem,\nparticularly in HIV patients."},{"time":36783,"text":"When they take their anti-HIV drugs,"},{"time":39960,"text":"these drugs are good for lowering\nthe virus in the blood,"},{"time":44050,"text":"and increasing the CD4 cell counts."},{"time":46618,"text":"But they are also notorious\nfor their adverse side effects,"},{"time":51007,"text":"but mostly bad, because they get diluted\nby the time they get to the blood,"},{"time":56524,"text":"and worse, by the time\nthey get to the sites"},{"time":59425,"text":"where it matters most:\nwithin the HIV viral reservoirs."},{"time":65751,"text":"These areas in the body --\nsuch as the lymph nodes,"},{"time":70298,"text":"the nervous system,\nas well as the lungs --"},{"time":73207,"text":"where the virus is sleeping,"},{"time":75735,"text":"and will not readily\nget delivered in the blood"},{"time":78967,"text":"of patients that are under\nconsistent anti-HIV drugs therapy."},{"time":84502,"text":"However, upon discontinuation of therapy,"},{"time":88212,"text":"the virus can awake\nand infect new cells in the blood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92728,"text":"Now, all this is a big problem in treating\nHIV with the current drug treatment,"},{"time":99337,"text":"which is a life-long treatment\nthat must be swallowed by patients."},{"time":103395,"text":"One day, I sat and thought,"},{"time":105790,"text":"\"Can we deliver anti-HIV directly\nwithin its reservoir sites,"},{"time":111551,"text":"without the risk of drug dilution?\""},{"time":114525,"text":"As a laser scientist,\nthe answer was just before my eyes:"},{"time":119142,"text":"Lasers, of course."},{"time":120976,"text":"If they can be used for dentistry,"},{"time":123864,"text":"for diabetic wound-healing and surgery,"},{"time":126739,"text":"they can be used for anything imaginable,"},{"time":129468,"text":"including transporting drugs into cells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133403,"text":"As a matter of fact,\nwe are currently using laser pulses"},{"time":138657,"text":"to poke or drill extremely tiny holes,"},{"time":142310,"text":"which open and close almost\nimmediately in HIV-infected cells,"},{"time":147246,"text":"in order to deliver drugs within them."},{"time":150380,"text":"\"How is that possible?\" you may ask."},{"time":153119,"text":"Well, we shine a very powerful\nbut super-tiny laser beam"},{"time":159476,"text":"onto the membrane of HIV-infected cells"},{"time":163304,"text":"while these cells are immersed\nin liquid containing the drug."},{"time":168395,"text":"The laser pierces the cell,\nwhile the cell swallows the drug"},{"time":173277,"text":"in a matter of microseconds."},{"time":175446,"text":"Before you even know it,"},{"time":177042,"text":"the induced hole\nbecomes immediately repaired."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181246,"text":"Now, we are currently testing\nthis technology in test tubes"},{"time":185690,"text":"or in Petri dishes,"},{"time":187221,"text":"but the goal is to get\nthis technology in the human body,"},{"time":191581,"text":"apply it in the human body."},{"time":193928,"text":"\"How is that possible?\" you may ask."},{"time":196422,"text":"Well, the answer is:\nthrough a three-headed device."},{"time":201506,"text":"Using the first head, which is our laser,"},{"time":204452,"text":"we will make an incision\nin the site of infection."},{"time":208498,"text":"Using the second head, which is a camera,"},{"time":211150,"text":"we meander to the site of infection."},{"time":213813,"text":"Finally, using a third head,\nwhich is a drug-spreading sprinkler,"},{"time":218604,"text":"we deliver the drugs directly\nat the site of infection,"},{"time":221635,"text":"while the laser is again used\nto poke those cells open."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226815,"text":"Well, this might not seem\nlike much right now."},{"time":230680,"text":"But one day, if successful,\nthis technology can lead"},{"time":235767,"text":"to complete eradication\nof HIV in the body."},{"time":239401,"text":"Yes. A cure for HIV."},{"time":242147,"text":"This is every HIV researcher's dream --"},{"time":245085,"text":"in our case, a cure lead by lasers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248636,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249813,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}